r_2-r_1=\frac{d}{2^{n+1}}\;,
\frac1{2^n}=\frac{2(r_2-r_1)}d\;.
\begin{align*} d+\frac{d}2+\frac{d}4+\ldots+\frac{d}{2^n}&=d\sum_{k=0}^n\left(\frac12\right)^k\\ &=d\left(2-\frac1{2^n}\right)\\ &=d\left(2-\frac{2(r_2-r_1)}d\right)\\ &=2d-2r_2+2r_1\;, \end{align*}
r_1=c+2d-2r_2+2r_1
d=\frac12(2r_2-r_1-c)\;.
